Put a #large saucepan{} of water on to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the pasta.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Cut into 2cm pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Finely chop the @chives{1} (use #scissors{} if easier).

== Pasta ==

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} and cook until tender, 
~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through 
to stop it sticking together.

== Chorizo ==

Heat a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{60%g} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer the chorizo to a #small bowl{} and pop the (now empty) #frying pan{} 
on medium heat with a drizzle of oil if needed.

== Sauce ==

Once the pan is hot, add the pepper and @sliced mushrooms{120%g}. Fry until golden and 
starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}, then stir in the cooked chorizo, 
@tomato passata{1}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, 
@sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce.

> See pantry for both sugar and water amounts.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, 
~{4-5%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Once the sauce has thickened, combine the cooked pasta and sauce in whichever pan is largest.

Stir in half the chives and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}, adding a splash 
of water if it's a little too thick.

Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

Share your linguine between your bowls.

Sprinkle with the remaining chives and cheese to finish.

Enjoy!